2500|$|<b>Forum</b> <b>non</b> <b>conveniens</b> (Latin for [...] "forum not agreeing") (FNC) is a (mostly) {{common law}} legal {{doctrine}} whereby courts may {{refuse to take}} jurisdiction over matters {{where there is a}} more appropriate forum available to the parties. As a doctrine of the conflict of laws, <b>forum</b> <b>non</b> <b>conveniens</b> applies between courts in different countries and between courts in different jurisdictions in the same country. <b>Forum</b> <b>non</b> <b>conveniens</b> is not applicable between counties or federal districts within a state.|$|E
