2500|$|Scholars and jurists {{seem to find}} a Scottish origin {{prior to}} the first American use of the concept. [...] Some writers see the {{doctrine}} of FNC as having developed from an earlier doctrine of <b>forum</b> <b>non</b> competens ("non-competent forum"). Many early cases in the U.S. and Scotland involving FNC were cases under admiralty law. FNC thus may ultimately have a civil law origin, as has been asserted by several writers, since admiralty law is based in civil law concepts.|$|R
